      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NAADRA (2) comes out of a much stronger race after showing early speed in the G2 Reisling Stakes at Randwick 18 days ago before fading late, and the drop back to midweek company makes her the one to beat. SHE'S EXTRA (1) is an unbeaten filly with two dominant wins to her name, the latest a soft 3-length victory at Warwick Farm over 1100m 3 weeks ago. The 3kg claim from regular hoop William Stanley will offset her weight rise, and the hat-trick beckons. LEONESSA (9) drifted back and raced greenly on debut at Warwick Farm, before working home soundly to finish sixth. JMac steps into the irons, and with a more genuine tempo here, she will be a quick improver. VICTORIOUS RULER (7) has trialled up well enough for her debut, and she hails from the Waterhouse/Bott stable, so you know that she will be ready to rumble. Check the markets. MOSCOW MAID (5) has a good gate for her debut, and her trial form has been very good. Watch closely.",
